==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hoy
<hw>Hoy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D. <ets>heu</ets>, or
Flem. <ets>hui</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A small coaster
vessel, usually sloop-rigged, used in conveying passengers and goods
from place to place, or as a tender to larger vessels in port.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>hoy</qex> went to London every week.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hoy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hoy
<hw>Hoy</hw>, <pos>interj.</pos> <ety>[D. <ets>hui</ets>. Cf.
<er>Ahoy</er>.]</ety> <def>Ho! Halloe! Stop!</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hoya</ent>⟦br⟧
